   - `spine` of `((Tree.leaf x) ⊔ t) ⊔ ts'` is `spine (((Tree.leaf x) ⊔ t) ⊔ ts')`.
   - By the inductive hypothesis, `spine ((Tree.leaf x) ⊔ t) = [Tree.leaf x, t]`.
   - So, `spine (((Tree.leaf x) ⊔ t) ⊔ ts') = [Tree.leaf x, t] ++ ts'`, which is `[Tree.leaf x] ++ [t] ++ ts'`, as desired.
